    <div class="main_after_install container">
        <div class="arrow-down-3"></div>
		<h1 class="home-headers">After Installation Steps</h1>
        <p class="main_after_install_text">While this site only details how to install Ghost, we have created multiple resources to help you after you have installed. If you are new to Ghost, check out <a href="http://ghostforbeginners.com">Ghost for Beginners</a>. <a href="http://ghostforbeginners.com">Ghost for Beginners</a> will guide you through the process of how to log in and create your first post, all the way to how to choose and customize your Ghost theme. It is a great resource for anyone who is looking for help when starting to use Ghost.<br><br>

        If you are a little bit more experienced with Ghost, we have an ongoing blog called <a href="http://allaboutghost.com">All About Ghost</a> that covers a wide range of higher level topics. While <a href="http://allaboutghost.com">All About Ghost</a> is a little bit more developer focused, there are great resources for anyone to use.<br><br>

        One of the first things most people do after creating a new website is try and make it look good. There are many different places to find Ghost themes and many people will not know where to find all of them. Because of this, we created <a href="http://allghostthemes.com">All Ghost Themes</a>. <a href="http://allghostthemes.com">All Ghost Themes</a> is a list of every Ghost theme out there. We update this site constantly to add in all the new themes and make it easy and fast for you to find Ghost themes.<br><br>

        Thank you for taking the time to check out our site(s)! If you have any questions or need any help, feel free to contact us on twitter (<a href="http://twitter.com/howtoghost">@howtoghost</a>), email (info@howtoinstallghost.com), or on the <a href="https://github.com/tryghost/Ghost#community">Ghost IRC</a> (davidbalderston and andyboutte). We would love to help you out in anyway that we can. Happy Ghosting!
